'''Amaliënstein''' is a former mission station of the Berlin Missionary Society, 22&nbsp;km east of [[Ladismith]], on the road to [[Calitzdorp]]. Named after Amalie von Stein, benefactress of German missions.<ref name="dosapn">{{cite book|last=Raper|first=Peter E.|title=Dictionary of Southern African Place Names|url=http://archive.org/stream/DictionaryOfSouthernAfricanPlaceNames/SaPlaceNames#page/n58/mode/2up|publisher=Internet Archive|accessdate=28 August 2013|page=58|year=1987}}</ref> The church complex was completed in 1853.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amalienstein & Zoar|url=http://www.route62.co.za/route62towns.php?townID=17|publisher=Route 62|accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref>

